WEBVTT

00:01.500 --> 00:04.420
Previously on "How To Get Away
With Murder"...

00:04.420 --> 00:05.710
You want to change your
life? Are you Annalise
Keating's bitch?

00:05.710 --> 00:06.420
[ Groans ]

00:06.420 --> 00:07.710
The baby.
Is it dead?

00:07.710 --> 00:09.080
Tell me!

00:09.080 --> 00:11.540
The governor knows
about the adoption.

00:11.540 --> 00:13.670
[ Applause ]
I am asking you
to protect my son

00:13.670 --> 00:15.000
from his own
worst instincts.

00:15.000 --> 00:16.330
Connor: Mom?

00:16.330 --> 00:18.250
The warden got a call
from an unlisted number.

00:18.250 --> 00:20.330
You had
Nate's dad killed.
No.

00:20.330 --> 00:21.460
Own it!
What?!

00:21.460 --> 00:22.710
[ Grunting ]

00:22.710 --> 00:24.880
It was him.
He murdered my pops.

00:24.880 --> 00:26.290
He murdered my pops.

00:26.290 --> 00:29.710
Take his car and him
and drive away.

00:29.710 --> 00:31.540
Why do you look like
someone just died?

00:31.540 --> 00:33.460
[ Slaps ]
What the hell
are you doing here?

00:33.460 --> 00:34.880
You left your keys
at the church.

00:34.880 --> 00:36.040
I know who you are.

00:36.040 --> 00:38.210
Frank:
Gabriel is Sam's kid.

00:40.790 --> 00:45.210
♪♪

00:45.210 --> 00:46.710
[ Lock clicks ]

00:46.710 --> 00:51.420
♪♪

00:51.420 --> 00:53.210
[ Water running ]

00:53.210 --> 01:02.040
♪♪

01:02.040 --> 01:10.750
♪♪

01:10.750 --> 01:12.330
Frank: Bonnie.

01:12.330 --> 01:14.420
What are you doing?

01:14.420 --> 01:17.620
Gabriel knows Sam's his dad,
so I told Annalise.

01:17.620 --> 01:18.920
You got to go
to her place

01:18.920 --> 01:21.170
and make sure she doesn't
jump off the roof.

01:22.420 --> 01:24.330
Bon!
I need you
to stop talking.

01:24.330 --> 01:26.000
She's only gonna
listen to you --

01:26.000 --> 01:27.580
Shut up so
I can tell you this.

01:27.580 --> 01:31.460
♪♪

01:31.460 --> 01:33.750
[ Cellphone ringing ]

01:39.120 --> 01:40.420
It's Frank.

01:40.420 --> 01:41.620
He could be here
in five minutes.

01:41.620 --> 01:43.330
I'm not gonna hurt you.
You broke into my home.

01:43.330 --> 01:45.040
I just want answers.
That's all.

01:45.040 --> 01:47.540
[ Ringing continues ]

01:48.790 --> 01:50.460
Hi.
Frank:
I need to come over,

01:50.460 --> 01:52.460
talk you through
the whole thing.

01:52.460 --> 01:54.120
Whatever you want to ask me,
I'll tell you.

01:54.120 --> 01:59.210
♪♪

01:59.210 --> 02:01.960
Annalise.

02:01.960 --> 02:03.620
I got nothing for you,
Frank.

02:03.620 --> 02:06.000
Please.

02:06.000 --> 02:07.000
[ Cellphone clicks ]

02:07.000 --> 02:08.620
♪♪

02:08.620 --> 02:10.500
[ Sighs ]

02:10.500 --> 02:18.500
♪♪

02:18.500 --> 02:26.830
♪♪

02:26.830 --> 02:35.040
♪♪

02:35.040 --> 02:36.580
Sit.

02:36.580 --> 02:42.250
♪♪

02:42.250 --> 02:48.250
♪♪

02:48.250 --> 02:49.670
[ Door opens ]

02:49.670 --> 02:50.830
Oliver: Wow.

02:50.830 --> 02:52.670
[ Chuckling ]
Your dad really knows

02:52.670 --> 02:54.830
how to buy
someone's forgiveness.
No, no, no.

02:54.830 --> 02:56.330
We are not forgiving him

02:56.330 --> 02:58.170
until he agrees to pay
for the honeymoon.

02:58.170 --> 02:59.830
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

02:59.830 --> 03:01.670
Who's that?

03:01.670 --> 03:02.580
Who do you think?

03:02.580 --> 03:04.330
[ Chuckles ]

03:04.330 --> 03:06.040
Well, I guess props to Pam
for getting back out there.

03:06.040 --> 03:07.330
No, Oli.

03:07.330 --> 03:10.210
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

03:10.210 --> 03:11.380
Michaela.
Ugh.

03:11.380 --> 03:13.620
[ Quietly ] Asher probably
took her phone.

03:13.620 --> 03:14.710
[ Cellphone clicks ]

03:16.120 --> 03:17.210
Come here.

03:20.710 --> 03:22.790
Hey.
Yeah?

03:22.790 --> 03:24.710
I really love you.

03:24.710 --> 03:26.710
I love you, too.

03:26.710 --> 03:28.540
[ Phone rings ]

03:28.540 --> 03:31.250
Enough!
It's our wedding night!

03:31.250 --> 03:32.420
You're dead to me, Asher.

03:32.420 --> 03:34.380
Yeah, me, too.
She's my mom now.

03:36.750 --> 03:38.290
What's wrong?

03:38.290 --> 03:40.540
Only Bonnie and Frank
knew before tonight.

03:40.540 --> 03:41.750
And you.

03:41.750 --> 03:44.210
They wanted proof
that Gabriel knew who he was

03:44.210 --> 03:45.580
before they told anyone.

03:45.580 --> 03:48.380
So when Frank found
his birth certificate tonight,

03:48.380 --> 03:50.000
he finally told Annalise.

03:52.120 --> 03:54.250
How long have you known?
A few weeks.

03:54.250 --> 03:55.420
-[ Scoffs ]
-Oh, my God.

03:55.420 --> 03:57.170
They told me that I had
to protect all of you.

03:57.170 --> 03:58.500
And since when do you do
what you're told?

03:58.500 --> 03:59.620
You think
you're pissed off?

03:59.620 --> 04:01.460
She let me make out
with him all week.

04:01.460 --> 04:02.620
How could you
let that happen?

04:02.620 --> 04:04.250
Okay, that is between
me and Michaela.

04:04.250 --> 04:06.420
I don't understand
how not telling us
about Gabriel

04:06.420 --> 04:08.080
is protecting us.

04:10.420 --> 04:11.670
You -- you were gonna
kill him?

04:11.670 --> 04:12.580
Not me.

04:12.580 --> 04:13.580
Nothing has changed.

04:13.580 --> 04:14.830
Gabriel still thinks
we're clueless.

04:14.830 --> 04:16.250
You don't know that.
I do!

04:16.250 --> 04:17.830
He ditched Michaela
at the wedding.

04:17.830 --> 04:18.830
Connor:
Well, maybe he was going...
Hey!

04:18.830 --> 04:19.830
...to hook up with my mom.

04:19.830 --> 04:20.920
Oh, wait.
No, that was you.

04:20.920 --> 04:21.960
Laurel: Okay, look.
We're all tired.

04:21.960 --> 04:22.920
We just need
to go to sleep.

04:22.920 --> 04:24.920
Listen!

04:24.920 --> 04:26.420
Gabriel hasn't returned
any of my calls.

04:26.420 --> 04:28.250
It's late.
He's probably asleep.

04:28.250 --> 04:30.750
Except I saw blood
on Bonnie's leg.

04:34.210 --> 04:36.540
Happy wedding.

04:36.540 --> 04:37.960
[ Liquid pours ]

04:39.170 --> 04:41.120
You don't care
about getting disbarred?

04:41.120 --> 04:42.960
Who's gonna tell them?
You?

04:42.960 --> 04:45.830
Only people that's gonna hurt
is class-action clients.

04:45.830 --> 04:47.670
Or did you just pretend
to care about them

04:47.670 --> 04:49.620
to get close to me?

04:49.620 --> 04:51.790
No.

04:51.790 --> 04:54.380
Truth shall set you free,
Gabriel.

04:54.380 --> 04:55.460
My mama raised me

04:55.460 --> 04:57.120
to care about people
worse off than us.

04:57.120 --> 04:58.620
Oh, so I'm supposed
to believe

04:58.620 --> 05:00.790
that she would be happy with you
studying under me?

05:00.790 --> 05:03.040
She doesn't know
I'm here.
Oh.

05:03.040 --> 05:05.540
Or you're just
a good liar.

05:05.540 --> 05:06.710
I never lied about
any of that --

05:06.710 --> 05:08.000
You lied about
who you are --

05:08.000 --> 05:11.290
My dad took off
before I was born.

05:11.290 --> 05:13.540
That's what my mama
always told me.

05:13.540 --> 05:15.080
I had no reason
to question it

05:15.080 --> 05:16.830
until my grandma died
last year.

05:16.830 --> 05:18.170
I was cleaning out
her apartment,

05:18.170 --> 05:20.670
and I found
my birth certificate.

05:20.670 --> 05:22.670
So why didn't you tell
your mother about any of this?

05:22.670 --> 05:24.580
'Cause it would kill her.
You know that.

05:24.580 --> 05:26.330
How would I know that?

05:26.330 --> 05:27.750
Sam left her for you.

05:27.750 --> 05:29.580
I don't know anything
about your mother.

05:29.580 --> 05:30.710
I didn't know about you
till tonight.

05:30.710 --> 05:32.040
Think about that.

05:32.040 --> 05:35.210
He lied to me
for 20 years.

05:35.210 --> 05:38.500
So he's the bad guy
in all this?

05:38.500 --> 05:39.830
That's what you want me
to believe?

05:39.830 --> 05:42.830
Well, we wouldn't be meeting
like this if he were good.

05:42.830 --> 05:46.710
♪♪

05:46.710 --> 05:47.830
[ Groans ]

05:47.830 --> 05:49.420
The baby?
Is he dead?

05:49.420 --> 05:50.670
Tell me!

05:50.670 --> 05:52.000
Take him!

05:52.880 --> 05:54.000
Sam:
We'll get through this.

05:56.880 --> 05:58.210
All right,
watch your step.

06:00.880 --> 06:02.880
Hey.
How was the drive?

06:02.880 --> 06:04.460
I'm sorry
you couldn't fly.

06:04.460 --> 06:06.540
My ma said that's normal
after a C-section.

06:06.540 --> 06:08.920
We made it home in one piece.
That's what matters.

06:08.920 --> 06:11.540
I can stock the kitchen with
a month's worth of junk food.

06:11.540 --> 06:13.080
Booze, too.
Booze you've been drinking?

06:13.080 --> 06:15.580
Huh?
You stink.

06:15.580 --> 06:17.750
[ Sighs ] Annie, Annie.
The doctor said no stairs.

06:17.750 --> 06:20.460
I'm not sleeping
on the couch.

06:20.460 --> 06:23.080
[ Sighs ] Fine.
Let me help you.

06:27.380 --> 06:29.420
I talked to
Dean Foster.

06:29.420 --> 06:32.420
He said to take as much time
as you need.

06:33.880 --> 06:35.460
Here.

06:36.040 --> 06:37.330
They're giving me time, too,

06:37.330 --> 06:40.290
which means I'll be free
to annoy you,

06:40.290 --> 06:41.830
however long you want.

06:47.580 --> 06:49.920
Here.
[ Pills rattle ]

06:49.920 --> 06:51.920
I'll get you some juice.

06:56.250 --> 06:57.500
Sam?

07:01.250 --> 07:02.170
Hey.

07:04.750 --> 07:06.790
You get to say
anything to me.

07:13.750 --> 07:16.460
The witness who died
has a son.

07:16.460 --> 07:18.120
Christophe. He's 12.

07:18.120 --> 07:24.040
♪♪

07:24.040 --> 07:26.210
Annie, it's too soon to think
about any of this.

07:26.210 --> 07:27.880
I got to think about
something else.

07:27.880 --> 07:29.330
Otherwise,
I can't breathe.

07:33.790 --> 07:36.790
He needs us, Sam,
just like we need him.

07:36.790 --> 07:37.790
We don't know what we need.

07:37.790 --> 07:38.960
I need him then.

07:42.170 --> 07:43.620
[ Exhales ]

07:48.170 --> 07:49.620
I'm not saying no.

07:49.620 --> 07:51.830
Of course you are.

07:51.830 --> 07:53.880
Let's just focus on
getting you better.

07:53.880 --> 07:56.380
The rest will
figure itself out.

07:56.380 --> 07:58.290
You mean
I'll figure it out,

07:58.290 --> 08:00.540
like always.

08:00.540 --> 08:08.710
♪♪

08:08.710 --> 08:17.040
♪♪

08:17.040 --> 08:25.420
♪♪

08:25.420 --> 08:27.420
[ Groans, sniffs ]

08:27.420 --> 08:30.710
♪♪

08:30.710 --> 08:32.330
[ Sighs ]

08:32.330 --> 08:37.920
♪♪

08:37.920 --> 08:40.380
[ Exhales ]

08:40.380 --> 08:43.380
[ Typing on keyboard ]

08:43.380 --> 08:50.750
♪♪

08:50.750 --> 08:58.460
♪♪

08:58.460 --> 09:00.210
[ Glass clinks on table ]

09:00.210 --> 09:01.540
[ Phone dialing ]

09:01.540 --> 09:07.250
♪♪

09:07.250 --> 09:10.210
[ Phone ringing ]

09:10.210 --> 09:11.380
Woman: At the tone,
please record your message.

09:11.380 --> 09:12.960
When you've finished recording,

09:12.960 --> 09:16.380
you may hang up
or press 1 for more options.

09:16.380 --> 09:17.380
[ Beep ]

09:17.380 --> 09:18.420
Vivian.

09:20.620 --> 09:24.790
I'm not sure this is actually
your number, but...

09:24.790 --> 09:27.080
It's Sam.

09:27.080 --> 09:30.250
Look, I know I don't have
a right to ask...

09:34.420 --> 09:36.580
...but I really want
to meet him, Viv.

09:38.250 --> 09:40.330
Please.

09:40.330 --> 09:42.920
I'll do anything
to meet him.

09:42.920 --> 09:46.250
♪♪

09:51.500 --> 09:54.670
Did he actually
tell you he'd call?

09:54.670 --> 09:56.080
It's Nate.
He'll know what to do.

09:56.080 --> 09:58.250
I'm not sure about that.

09:58.250 --> 10:00.080
[ Knocking on door ]

10:00.750 --> 10:02.500
[ Glass clinks on table ]

10:02.500 --> 10:04.580
That him?

10:04.580 --> 10:07.460
Large pineapple pizza
and a Caesar salad for Bonnie?

10:07.460 --> 10:10.210
Yeah.
$22.75.

10:10.210 --> 10:11.960
Here's $40.
Keep the change.

10:11.960 --> 10:13.290
Uh, you don't
have to do that.

10:13.290 --> 10:14.620
I-I used to waitress.

10:14.620 --> 10:16.290
Tipping is one of
my only joys.

10:18.290 --> 10:19.540
[ Door closes ]

10:19.540 --> 10:22.120
Alibi.

10:22.120 --> 10:23.880
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

10:27.170 --> 10:29.120
-Hey.
-Are you with Bonnie?

10:29.120 --> 10:31.540
Frank: Yeah. Why?

10:31.540 --> 10:33.710
I saw blood on Bonnie's leg
at the wedding,

10:33.710 --> 10:35.120
and now Gabriel's missing.

10:35.120 --> 10:36.460
You got me
on speaker phone?

10:36.460 --> 10:38.960
Did you two
do something to him?
God, no.

10:38.960 --> 10:41.120
Just tell us why Gabriel
isn't answering his phone.

10:41.120 --> 10:42.330
He's probably sleeping.

10:42.330 --> 10:43.380
Sleeping, like,
six feet under?

10:43.380 --> 10:44.460
No one hurt Gabriel.

10:44.460 --> 10:46.880
So go to bed,
sleep off your hangovers.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.330
I'll call you in the morning
once I know more.

10:51.000 --> 10:53.750
[ Sighs ]
That's too bad.
What is?

10:53.750 --> 10:56.540
Well, a dead Gabriel would have
at least stayed quiet.

11:01.170 --> 11:03.330
Annalise: I know what
you're telling yourself.

11:03.330 --> 11:05.540
That I ruined the marriage,
I stole your father.

11:05.540 --> 11:07.710
Makes for a good story,
but it just isn't true.

11:09.080 --> 11:10.170
Which part?

11:12.670 --> 11:15.080
That I'm to blame for you
having no father.

11:16.580 --> 11:18.330
I never said I blame you.
Oh.

11:18.330 --> 11:19.880
Then why come here,
play all of us?

11:19.880 --> 11:22.170
I want to know
how he died, Annalise.

11:22.170 --> 11:23.500
Go online.
It's all there.

11:23.500 --> 11:24.750
So it's true.

11:24.750 --> 11:26.920
Wes killed him.
Yes.

11:26.920 --> 11:28.580
Then why's Frank looking
into me this whole time?
I don't know. Ask him.

11:28.580 --> 11:29.880
You didn't tell him
to keep an eye on me?

11:29.880 --> 11:31.580
I said I never knew you existed
until tonight.

11:31.580 --> 11:32.960
That's hard to believe.
Well, it's true.

11:32.960 --> 11:34.210
Frank's been lying to me

11:34.210 --> 11:35.290
just like you've
been lying to me

11:35.290 --> 11:36.710
just like Sam.

11:36.710 --> 11:39.790
♪♪

11:39.790 --> 11:42.880
You have more in common with
your father than you knew.

11:42.880 --> 11:44.040
Where are you going?

11:44.040 --> 11:49.540
♪♪

11:49.540 --> 11:50.580
Hey.

11:50.580 --> 11:51.920
Bonnie: Hey.

11:51.920 --> 11:54.040
Thanks for bringing
that over.

11:54.040 --> 11:55.620
It's the least
I could do.

11:58.620 --> 12:00.210
How are you?

12:00.210 --> 12:01.710
We're doing okay.

12:01.710 --> 12:03.380
Doctor says she's
healing pretty good.

12:03.380 --> 12:04.540
It's easy for me to say

12:04.540 --> 12:08.040
since I'm not
the one who's in pain.

12:08.040 --> 12:11.080
I'm so sorry this happened.

12:11.080 --> 12:14.580
I'm just grateful nothing
happened to Annie.

12:14.580 --> 12:16.750
[ Sighs ]

12:16.750 --> 12:18.080
I, uh...

12:19.830 --> 12:21.670
I never even
got to hold him.

12:24.330 --> 12:25.460
They just took him.
I don't --

12:25.460 --> 12:27.790
I don't even know where.

12:27.790 --> 12:30.000
[ Sighs ]

12:30.000 --> 12:33.750
♪♪

12:33.750 --> 12:36.250
Annalise: Bonnie?

12:36.250 --> 12:38.080
I didn't hear you
come in.

12:38.080 --> 12:40.420
I just got here.

12:40.420 --> 12:42.120
Do you want me
to bring this upstairs?

12:47.170 --> 12:48.580
Hey.

12:48.580 --> 12:49.830
Should you be out of bed?

12:49.830 --> 12:51.330
Go home.
We're not working yet.

12:51.330 --> 12:53.120
I know. I just --
I was in the hood --

12:53.120 --> 12:54.830
I asked him to come over.

12:54.830 --> 12:58.170
♪♪

12:58.170 --> 12:59.540
Come on up.

12:59.540 --> 13:05.620
♪♪

13:05.620 --> 13:06.880
[ Door closes ]

13:06.880 --> 13:09.620
Bonnie: The pump's not as
complicated as it looks.

13:09.620 --> 13:12.120
And it'll help relieve
some of the pain,

13:12.120 --> 13:15.000
even though it might
take a little longer
to stop producing.

13:16.620 --> 13:18.460
Here.

13:18.460 --> 13:19.830
Send that certified mail.

13:19.830 --> 13:21.170
Let me know
when it gets there.

13:25.500 --> 13:27.000
Sam can't know.

13:29.540 --> 13:30.710
Frank:
Please let me tell.

13:30.710 --> 13:31.790
You don't need to.

13:31.790 --> 13:33.500
Your face is everything
you're feeling.

13:33.500 --> 13:35.000
[ Voice breaking ]
'Cause it's killing me.
It should be.

13:35.000 --> 13:38.420
My son died,
and you're responsible.

13:38.420 --> 13:39.710
That's why
I need to tell her.
Why?

13:39.710 --> 13:41.250
So you can feel better

13:41.250 --> 13:42.750
while the rest of us
suffer?

13:42.750 --> 13:46.500
Your guilt goes away,
but we're stuck in this hell?

13:46.500 --> 13:48.250
You take this
to your grave.

13:50.580 --> 13:52.170
Bonnie: Won't Sam
want this, too?

13:52.170 --> 13:53.750
Annalise:
He's too fragile.

13:53.750 --> 13:55.330
He won't even consider it.

13:55.330 --> 13:57.670
He's in shock.
Well, so am I.

13:57.670 --> 14:00.170
But it's the only thing
making me not slit my wrists.

14:02.500 --> 14:03.750
It's just the first step,
Bonnie.

14:03.750 --> 14:05.540
Adoption is a long process.

14:05.540 --> 14:10.670
♪♪

14:10.670 --> 14:11.830
Bonnie?

14:15.000 --> 14:17.080
I know you love Sam
the same way I do.

14:19.620 --> 14:22.080
But I need you
to choose me right now.

14:24.710 --> 14:26.080
Okay.

14:27.960 --> 14:29.250
Thank you.

14:29.250 --> 14:38.250
♪♪

14:45.540 --> 14:46.750
What's this?

14:46.750 --> 14:48.580
You don't believe
Wes did it.

14:48.580 --> 14:49.620
Here's your proof.

14:49.620 --> 14:51.380
Annalise, it's Wes.

14:51.380 --> 14:53.210
I just got to the house.

14:53.210 --> 14:54.920
I was at
the police station.

14:54.920 --> 14:56.710
They found Rebecca's body.

14:56.710 --> 14:59.330
They're saying you did it.

14:59.330 --> 15:01.080
All of it.

15:01.080 --> 15:02.500
Even Sam.

15:02.500 --> 15:06.080
You can't go down
for what I did.

15:06.080 --> 15:07.500
There's no way I could
live with myself,

15:07.500 --> 15:11.670
so just please,
come home.

15:11.670 --> 15:13.620
That was enough for the D.A.
to tell the judge

15:13.620 --> 15:15.080
to close Sam's case.

15:15.080 --> 15:16.670
Why?

15:16.670 --> 15:18.080
Because it's him
confessing.

15:18.080 --> 15:19.620
No. Why?
Why did he do it?

15:19.620 --> 15:21.250
Why do you think?
He was sick in the head.

15:21.250 --> 15:22.830
I'm just trying to understand
why one of your students

15:22.830 --> 15:24.500
would kill your husband.

15:24.500 --> 15:25.920
Well, I've been trying
to figure that out
all these years,

15:25.920 --> 15:27.670
and I still don't know.

15:27.670 --> 15:29.330
All I know is that
I'm done with everyone

15:29.330 --> 15:30.420
accusing me
of killing my husband.

15:30.420 --> 15:31.580
I never accused you.

15:31.580 --> 15:33.750
Sam broke my heart,
Gabriel.

15:33.750 --> 15:36.920
♪♪

15:36.920 --> 15:38.620
Just like he broke yours.

15:38.620 --> 15:42.670
♪♪

15:42.670 --> 15:44.290
He betrayed us both.

15:45.960 --> 15:48.210
[ Water running ]

15:49.620 --> 15:51.460
[ Water shuts off ]

15:51.460 --> 15:52.960
What's wrong?

15:52.960 --> 15:55.960
A lawyer from Ohio
called my office this morning.

15:55.960 --> 15:57.960
She wanted my
Social Security number.

15:57.960 --> 16:00.620
I thought it was a scam
until she clarified.

16:00.620 --> 16:03.670
It's about the adoption.

16:03.670 --> 16:04.790
I told you
I wanted to do this.

16:04.790 --> 16:06.000
It's been a week.

16:06.000 --> 16:07.380
You're barely
back on your feet.

16:07.380 --> 16:08.670
Don't be my doctor.
Be my husband.

16:08.670 --> 16:10.170
That's all
this is about --

16:10.170 --> 16:11.960
me loving and
protecting my wife.
Then give me this.

16:11.960 --> 16:13.460
You're in grief, Annie.

16:13.460 --> 16:14.960
You have no idea what the hell
you want right now.

16:14.960 --> 16:16.380
What I want is
to feel better.

16:16.380 --> 16:18.380
And you know what does that?
That little boy.

16:18.380 --> 16:19.330
[ In distance ]
He's the only thing

16:19.330 --> 16:20.500
that's getting me
through this nightmare.

16:20.500 --> 16:21.540
[ In distance ]
It's our nightmare.

16:21.540 --> 16:22.670
We're both
going through this.

16:22.670 --> 16:24.000
Then you should know
exactly why I need this.

16:24.000 --> 16:25.540
No, what we need is time.

16:25.540 --> 16:27.210
Time for what?
To grieve more?

16:27.210 --> 16:28.380
'Cause I'm the one
doing that.

16:28.380 --> 16:29.670
Maybe it doesn't look like
you think it should,

16:29.670 --> 16:31.330
but I'm feeling everything
I need to right now.

16:31.330 --> 16:33.080
No child is gonna make
this pain go away!

16:33.080 --> 16:34.380
How do you know that?
Well, let's just think about
that boy right now --

16:34.380 --> 16:35.750
He lost a mother!
We lost a son!

16:35.750 --> 16:37.420
Exactly. Our son!

16:37.420 --> 16:39.420
Not some dog
from the pound.

16:39.420 --> 16:41.920
We have to grieve him,
have a funeral.
No!

16:41.920 --> 16:43.750
You loved him, Annie.
I know you did.
Of course I loved him.

16:43.750 --> 16:45.330
Well, then let's take the time
to accept what we've lost.

16:45.330 --> 16:47.670
He's dead,
and you know who isn't?

16:47.670 --> 16:49.920
That little boy
who I know I can love

16:49.920 --> 16:51.210
because he's alive.

16:51.210 --> 16:53.000
Well, that's not
gonna happen here

16:53.000 --> 16:54.500
if you want to stay
married to me.

16:54.500 --> 17:02.210
♪♪

17:02.210 --> 17:06.210
Well, I'm going through
with it,

17:06.210 --> 17:08.380
with or without you.

17:08.380 --> 17:11.580
[ Breathing heavily ]

17:11.580 --> 17:14.540
♪♪

17:14.540 --> 17:15.880
Okay.

17:17.790 --> 17:19.540
But it's without me.

17:19.540 --> 17:25.710
♪♪

17:25.710 --> 17:31.380
♪♪

17:31.380 --> 17:33.040
Sam?

17:34.460 --> 17:37.790
Go home.
Give her some space.

17:37.790 --> 17:41.080
[ Door opens, closes ]

17:41.080 --> 17:47.080
♪♪

17:53.580 --> 17:58.920
[ Indistinct conversations
in distance ]

17:58.920 --> 18:02.420
♪♪

18:02.420 --> 18:03.620
Connor: Of course he's here
to take us down.

18:03.620 --> 18:05.620
Oliver: Maybe he just wants to
find out about his father.

18:05.620 --> 18:07.580
Laurel: Or he's known Sam
his whole life.

18:07.580 --> 18:10.000
Still, that doesn't mean
he can do anything to hurt us.

18:10.000 --> 18:11.000
He could go to the D.A.

18:11.000 --> 18:12.580
and have them
reopen the case.

18:12.580 --> 18:14.080
I thought Sam's case
was closed?

18:14.080 --> 18:15.580
Nobody was ever convicted.

18:15.580 --> 18:17.580
So all Gabriel has to do
is find new evidence

18:17.580 --> 18:19.290
and bring it to the D.A.
Oh, this hurts my head.

18:19.290 --> 18:21.920
Seriously,
my head is racing.

18:21.920 --> 18:23.120
'Cause you're ashamed
that you hooked up

18:23.120 --> 18:25.080
with your friend's mom?

18:25.080 --> 18:26.960
Yeah, well,
I have great news, okay?

18:26.960 --> 18:29.210
Even if Gabriel tries
to reopen Sam's case,

18:29.210 --> 18:30.330
we have a friend
in the D.A.'s.

18:30.330 --> 18:31.620
You're just
a stupid intern.

18:31.620 --> 18:33.040
Miller isn't gonna
break the law for you.

18:33.040 --> 18:34.710
Yeah, but he'll do it
for his girlfriend.

18:35.880 --> 18:37.460
-Bonnie.
-Since when are they together?

18:37.460 --> 18:38.830
-Bonnie's with Miller?
-Why would she date him?

18:38.830 --> 18:39.960
This is great, okay?

18:39.960 --> 18:41.330
There's no way that Bonnie's

18:41.330 --> 18:43.540
gonna let Miller
charge us with anything.

18:43.540 --> 18:51.380
♪♪

18:51.380 --> 18:53.000
[ Quietly ]
Annalise was right.

18:56.120 --> 18:57.330
Ron was playing me.

18:57.330 --> 18:59.540
I just
didn't want to see it.

19:02.830 --> 19:04.880
I saw the guy around you.

19:04.880 --> 19:08.000
No way he's faking that.

19:08.000 --> 19:10.580
I need to believe
he was awful, Frank.

19:14.580 --> 19:15.750
Please.

19:18.710 --> 19:21.040
Gabriel:
What was he like?

19:21.040 --> 19:22.750
Really?

19:22.750 --> 19:24.330
I mean, you were married to him
for all those years.

19:24.330 --> 19:25.540
It couldn't have been
that bad.

19:25.540 --> 19:26.670
Yeah, that's what
I thought.

19:26.670 --> 19:28.170
It's why I didn't think

19:28.170 --> 19:30.250
he was capable
of killing that girl.

19:30.250 --> 19:31.210
Lila?
[ Keys jingle ]

19:33.330 --> 19:34.420
You're making him out
to be some monster.

19:34.420 --> 19:36.330
He walked out on you
and your mother.

19:36.330 --> 19:37.500
Maybe she didn't
tell him about me.

19:37.500 --> 19:38.920
Or maybe
he just didn't care.

19:40.500 --> 19:41.710
You're only saying that
because he hurt you.

19:41.710 --> 19:44.000
He hurt all of us.

19:44.000 --> 19:46.580
And don't you dare take
his side over your mother.

19:46.580 --> 19:49.120
She's the real victim here,
not him.

19:49.120 --> 19:57.710
♪♪

19:57.710 --> 19:59.460
[ Groans ]

19:59.460 --> 20:06.080
♪♪

20:06.080 --> 20:08.040
[ Pills rattle ]

20:09.620 --> 20:11.960
[ Bottle clinks on table ]

20:11.960 --> 20:13.710
Frank: You love this,
don't you?

20:13.710 --> 20:15.120
What are you talking about?

20:15.120 --> 20:17.040
Sam and Annalise
in the weeds.

20:17.040 --> 20:18.420
It means you can finally
get it in with him.

20:20.710 --> 20:22.080
Don't feel bad.

20:22.080 --> 20:23.540
Lots of people crush
on their shrink.

20:23.540 --> 20:25.710
You want to dig into each
other's personal lives?

20:25.710 --> 20:27.380
Let's do it.
I'm just playing with you.

20:28.880 --> 20:30.250
What happened in Ohio?

20:33.120 --> 20:34.420
[ Unzips ]

20:34.420 --> 20:35.790
Lisa: So you want to
change your life?

20:35.790 --> 20:37.080
Frank: It's my fault.

20:40.000 --> 20:42.500
You tell her,
and I'll ruin you.

20:47.250 --> 20:48.790
You know what happened.

20:48.790 --> 20:50.580
The Mahoney case tanked,

20:50.580 --> 20:53.290
and Annalise got hit
by a car.

20:53.290 --> 20:55.290
I mean
between you and Sam.

20:55.290 --> 21:00.170
♪♪

21:00.170 --> 21:01.920
You like a guy with mystery,
don't you?

21:01.920 --> 21:03.420
Stop.
I know what you're doing.

21:03.420 --> 21:04.790
Making up that Sam and I
have some secret

21:04.790 --> 21:06.290
'cause it turns you on.

21:07.920 --> 21:09.960
'Cause if that's true...

21:11.750 --> 21:13.210
I might be able to help.

21:16.620 --> 21:18.790
You're drunk.

21:18.790 --> 21:20.120
Only a little.

21:22.540 --> 21:24.790
[ Phone ringing ]

21:26.880 --> 21:29.500
Sam: Hey.

21:29.500 --> 21:31.540
Annalise: Your sister tell you
to divorce me yet?

21:31.540 --> 21:34.290
No, but she's still berating me
for not getting a prenup.

21:36.710 --> 21:39.460
You call your mother?
No.

21:39.460 --> 21:42.170
It's really nice to be around
family right now, Annie.

21:42.170 --> 21:43.830
Why do you want her
to come here?

21:43.830 --> 21:46.210
Am I gonna be alone
in the house that long?

21:50.620 --> 21:52.120
[ Sighs ]

21:53.500 --> 21:55.250
You know I'm okay.

21:57.580 --> 21:59.170
Make sure you
tell Hannah that.

21:59.170 --> 22:01.580
I can't take her
feeling sorry for me.

22:01.580 --> 22:02.830
Will do.

22:02.830 --> 22:04.330
I'll call you tomorrow.

22:06.500 --> 22:08.670
[ Phone beeps ]

22:08.670 --> 22:16.750
♪♪

22:16.750 --> 22:18.670
[ Knocks on door ]

22:20.830 --> 22:21.880
You need to go.

22:21.880 --> 22:23.750
Please, Gwen.
She won't return my calls.

22:23.750 --> 22:27.420
Because she doesn't
want to talk to you,
let alone see you.

22:27.420 --> 22:30.000
Is she in there
right now?
No.

22:30.000 --> 22:31.920
Is he?
Sam, please leave.

22:31.920 --> 22:34.250
[ Knocks on door ]
[ Loudly ] Vivian, it's me.
Please come out.

22:34.250 --> 22:36.210
Keep yelling,
and I call the police.

22:36.210 --> 22:37.620
Or maybe I just
call your wife.

22:37.620 --> 22:40.380
Does she know you're here?
I just want to know my son.

22:40.380 --> 22:42.710
You lost that chance
when you left your wife.

22:42.710 --> 22:44.710
And t-the only thing
that Vivian asked for --

22:44.710 --> 22:46.210
the one thing
you did right --

22:46.210 --> 22:48.380
was stay away.

22:48.380 --> 22:51.880
So if you have an ounce
of love or respect

22:51.880 --> 22:53.710
or basic human decency left,

22:53.710 --> 22:56.250
you will leave right now.

22:56.250 --> 23:02.750
♪♪

23:02.750 --> 23:04.250
I'm sorry.

23:07.380 --> 23:08.880
Go home, Sam.

23:13.750 --> 23:14.790
[ Door closes ]

23:14.790 --> 23:17.040
[ Basketball bouncing ]

23:17.040 --> 23:25.080
♪♪

23:25.080 --> 23:26.460
Hey.

23:26.460 --> 23:27.580
Hi.

23:31.120 --> 23:32.580
Are you...

23:32.580 --> 23:40.500
♪♪

23:40.500 --> 23:42.290
You a Bulls fan?

23:42.290 --> 23:44.120
Yeah.

23:44.120 --> 23:45.750
Can I have my ball back?

23:45.750 --> 23:51.620
♪♪

23:51.620 --> 23:57.750
♪♪

23:57.750 --> 23:59.210
[ Knocks on door ]

23:59.210 --> 24:01.040
Grandma?

24:01.040 --> 24:02.830
Gabriel?

24:02.830 --> 24:05.460
Get in here right now.

24:05.460 --> 24:07.290
[ Door slams ]

24:07.290 --> 24:12.960
♪♪

24:18.460 --> 24:20.670
[ Crickets chirping ]

24:36.960 --> 24:39.500
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

24:39.500 --> 24:44.330
♪♪

24:44.330 --> 24:45.500
Hey.

24:45.500 --> 24:47.250
Nate: Hey.

24:47.250 --> 24:48.170
Where are you?

24:48.170 --> 24:50.000
Doesn't matter.

24:50.000 --> 24:52.330
But this is the last time
you two spoke.

24:52.330 --> 24:53.250
He's drunk.

24:53.250 --> 24:54.750
He's trying to apologize.

24:54.750 --> 24:56.000
Does he want me
to come get him?

24:56.000 --> 24:57.670
Who is that?
Frank.

24:57.670 --> 24:59.040
Bonnie.

24:59.040 --> 25:00.420
He can help us.

25:03.330 --> 25:05.380
Does this mean
Annalise knows?
Of course not.

25:05.380 --> 25:08.000
Just tell me where you are
so Frank can come get you.

25:11.000 --> 25:13.670
Annalise: You know, me and you
are more alike than you think.

25:13.670 --> 25:15.210
[ Chuckles ]

25:15.210 --> 25:17.330
I grew up
without a father, too.

25:19.250 --> 25:21.670
Messed me up and...

25:21.670 --> 25:25.120
probably what led me
to the wrong man.

25:25.120 --> 25:26.750
This void that
you're trying to fill,

25:26.750 --> 25:28.960
coming here,
breaking into my home?

25:32.580 --> 25:33.880
He's dead, Gabriel.

25:36.620 --> 25:39.210
Better to have no father
than a bad one.

25:43.540 --> 25:48.790
[ Breast pump buzzing ]

25:52.250 --> 25:58.290
♪♪

25:58.290 --> 26:04.420
♪♪

26:04.420 --> 26:10.460
♪♪

26:10.460 --> 26:12.080
[ Cellphone rings ]

26:14.250 --> 26:15.290
Hello?

26:15.290 --> 26:17.080
Sloane:
Is this Annalise Keating?

26:17.080 --> 26:18.500
Yes.
Hi, Miss Keating.

26:18.500 --> 26:19.750
This is Maria Sloane

26:19.750 --> 26:20.960
from the Department of
Children and Family Services

26:20.960 --> 26:22.080
in Cleveland.

26:22.080 --> 26:24.920
Do you have a minute?
Of course.

26:24.920 --> 26:26.670
She's not answering.

26:26.670 --> 26:29.080
Maybe Sam is back.
They're having make-up sex.

26:30.620 --> 26:32.580
Have you ever met
his sister?
Hmm?

26:32.580 --> 26:33.790
Hannah.

26:33.790 --> 26:35.080
That's who
he's with right now?

26:35.080 --> 26:36.330
Your guess is
as good as mine.

26:36.330 --> 26:37.580
You don't think
he's there?

26:37.580 --> 26:38.920
Okay, you're kind of
proving my point

26:38.920 --> 26:40.960
that you're obsessed
with the guy.

26:40.960 --> 26:42.080
I'm worried about him.

26:44.170 --> 26:47.380
Well, I'm worried
about Annalise.

26:47.380 --> 26:50.960
Because there's something
you won't tell me?

26:50.960 --> 26:52.880
Maybe I can help you.

26:52.880 --> 26:54.960
No one can help me, okay?

26:54.960 --> 26:56.790
I'm screwed up,
I screw other people up.

26:56.790 --> 26:59.330
That's my life.

26:59.330 --> 27:01.790
Annalise gets that.

27:01.790 --> 27:04.620
I just...

27:04.620 --> 27:06.620
I hate that
she's not okay.

27:06.620 --> 27:09.620
♪♪

27:09.620 --> 27:10.710
Frank.

27:12.830 --> 27:14.960
[ Glass clinks on table ]

27:14.960 --> 27:17.120
You're a better guy
than you think.

27:17.120 --> 27:23.670
♪♪

27:23.670 --> 27:30.500
♪♪

27:30.500 --> 27:31.830
[ Jacket unzips ]

27:31.830 --> 27:32.880
♪♪

27:32.880 --> 27:34.880
[ Water splashes ]

27:34.880 --> 27:42.000
♪♪

27:42.000 --> 27:49.170
♪♪

27:49.170 --> 27:51.880
[ Phone rings ]

27:51.880 --> 27:53.710
This is the cellphone
of Sam Keating.

27:53.710 --> 27:54.710
Leave a message.

27:54.710 --> 27:56.500
[ Beeps ]

27:56.500 --> 27:58.710
Sam, can you call me back?

28:02.000 --> 28:04.330
[ Voice breaking ]
Please come home. Please.

28:05.880 --> 28:07.670
I'll try to be better.

28:09.960 --> 28:12.210
I just need you here.

28:12.210 --> 28:19.920
♪♪

28:19.920 --> 28:27.540
♪♪

28:27.540 --> 28:35.540
♪♪

28:35.540 --> 28:37.210
[ Cellphone beeps ]

28:37.210 --> 28:38.790
♪♪

28:38.790 --> 28:40.420
[ Cellphone closes ]

28:40.420 --> 28:46.250
♪♪

28:46.250 --> 28:52.170
♪♪

28:52.170 --> 28:53.670
Annalise?

28:53.670 --> 28:59.080
♪♪

28:59.080 --> 29:00.750
Annalise?

29:00.750 --> 29:05.330
♪♪

29:05.330 --> 29:07.080
[ Door opens ]

29:15.120 --> 29:16.460
[ Pounding on door ]

29:16.460 --> 29:18.750
Annalise?
Are you in there?

29:18.750 --> 29:23.750
♪♪

29:23.750 --> 29:25.670
Annalise? Wake up.

29:25.670 --> 29:28.250
♪♪

29:28.250 --> 29:31.250
Annalise, it's Bonnie.

29:31.250 --> 29:33.290
Annalise, please wake up.

29:33.290 --> 29:34.290
Please.
Please, just wake up!

29:41.500 --> 29:43.540
[ Door opens ]

29:46.670 --> 29:51.830
♪♪

29:51.830 --> 29:52.790
[ Keys clack in tray ]

29:52.790 --> 30:01.540
♪♪

30:01.540 --> 30:03.540
[ Sniffling ]

30:03.540 --> 30:12.620
♪♪

30:12.620 --> 30:14.000
[ Groans ]

30:17.580 --> 30:19.170
What is it?

30:22.210 --> 30:23.830
You can tell me.

30:26.500 --> 30:28.420
The adoption
isn't happening.

30:31.750 --> 30:33.500
Bonnie:
The paramedics are coming.

30:33.500 --> 30:35.170
They're gonna be here
any second. Annalise!

30:35.170 --> 30:37.210
Okay. You just stay
looking at me.

30:37.210 --> 30:39.880
Just right here.
You're gonna be fine.

30:39.880 --> 30:41.330
It's okay.

30:41.330 --> 30:42.920
Okay? Look at me.

30:42.920 --> 30:45.330
Just keep looking
at me, okay?

30:45.330 --> 30:48.210
That's right.
It's gonna be okay.

30:48.210 --> 30:49.500
I don't know why
I'm so surprised.

30:49.500 --> 30:53.170
I never thought
it would happen for me.

30:53.170 --> 30:56.250
Being a mom.

30:56.250 --> 30:58.710
Sam convinced me.

30:58.710 --> 31:00.790
I believed him.

31:00.790 --> 31:04.120
[ Annalise gags, coughs ]

31:04.120 --> 31:05.880
Okay, it's okay.
Get it all out.

31:07.880 --> 31:08.880
What do you need?

31:08.880 --> 31:11.080
[ Grunts ]

31:11.080 --> 31:13.210
Okay.
Let me help you.

31:13.210 --> 31:15.960
Let me help you.
My baby. My baby.

31:15.960 --> 31:17.540
I've got to get --
where's my baby, Bonnie?

31:17.540 --> 31:19.120
I've got to get my baby.
No, it's okay.

31:19.120 --> 31:20.750
[ Groans ] Bonnie.
You're all right.

31:20.750 --> 31:22.540
[ Groans ]

31:22.540 --> 31:24.380
My baby.
Where's my baby, Bonnie?

31:25.880 --> 31:27.420
Got my hopes up,

31:27.420 --> 31:31.080
even when my body
wasn't working for me.

31:31.080 --> 31:33.540
I didn't listen.

31:33.540 --> 31:35.540
Just kept trying.

31:35.540 --> 31:41.170
♪♪

31:41.170 --> 31:44.500
[ Voice breaking ]
Then it finally happened.

31:44.500 --> 31:46.790
He was right here, Bonnie.
I need to go get him.

31:46.790 --> 31:48.580
Annalise.
I can hear him crying.

31:48.580 --> 31:50.080
I've got to feed my baby.

31:50.080 --> 31:50.920
Listen to me.
Bonnie.

31:50.920 --> 31:52.080
Listen to me.

31:52.080 --> 31:54.290
There's no baby.

31:54.290 --> 31:56.670
It's the pills.
There's no baby.

31:56.670 --> 31:58.920
I'm sorry.

31:58.920 --> 32:00.670
There's no baby.

32:00.670 --> 32:02.750
♪♪

32:02.750 --> 32:05.080
[ Breathes deeply ]

32:05.080 --> 32:07.920
[ Sobbing ]
I killed him...

32:07.920 --> 32:10.960
No.

32:10.960 --> 32:13.080
No.
No, it was an accident.

32:13.080 --> 32:14.790
I killed him.
No, it --

32:14.790 --> 32:17.250
It's --
Bonnie, it's my fault.

32:17.250 --> 32:19.000
It's not.

32:19.000 --> 32:22.620
My fault, Bonnie.
[ Sobs ]

32:22.620 --> 32:27.210
♪♪

32:27.210 --> 32:30.000
I keep thinking
I'm gonna just wake up

32:30.000 --> 32:32.670
and it's just a bad dream.

32:32.670 --> 32:35.620
♪♪

32:35.620 --> 32:38.000
God wouldn't let this
happen to me.

32:42.120 --> 32:44.170
And then I remember.

32:44.170 --> 32:49.880
♪♪

32:49.880 --> 32:51.000
[ Sniffles ]

32:51.000 --> 32:55.500
♪♪

32:55.500 --> 32:56.540
[ Sniffles ]

32:56.540 --> 32:58.120
Bonnie?

33:00.120 --> 33:03.000
I'm glad
you're in my life.

33:03.000 --> 33:06.830
♪♪

33:06.830 --> 33:08.670
So am I.

33:08.670 --> 33:13.710
♪♪

33:13.710 --> 33:15.880
[ Cellphone ringing ]

33:20.420 --> 33:22.330
Where are you?
The house.

33:22.330 --> 33:24.080
Oh, crap.
Am I late?

33:24.080 --> 33:27.080
Annalise actually said you
don't need to come in today.

33:27.080 --> 33:28.540
Did you tell her?

33:28.540 --> 33:29.830
What?

33:29.830 --> 33:31.330
About us.

33:31.330 --> 33:33.170
Of course not.

33:33.170 --> 33:34.000
You're not having regrets,
I hope.

33:36.000 --> 33:37.040
No.

33:38.080 --> 33:39.080
Are you?

33:39.080 --> 33:40.210
Hell no.

33:40.210 --> 33:41.580
I just want it
to happen again.

33:44.380 --> 33:46.460
We'll see.

33:46.460 --> 33:47.420
[ Cellphone closes ]

33:51.880 --> 33:53.540
[ Knocking on door ]

33:55.580 --> 33:57.080
Just a sec.

33:57.080 --> 34:03.750
♪♪

34:03.750 --> 34:05.040
[ Door opens ]

34:06.710 --> 34:08.040
Do I know you?

34:08.040 --> 34:15.540
♪♪

34:15.540 --> 34:16.750
What now?

34:19.790 --> 34:21.210
[ Paper rustles ]

34:24.380 --> 34:25.750
Why do you have this?
It doesn't matter.

34:25.750 --> 34:27.670
You showed Annalise.

34:27.670 --> 34:29.290
No.

34:29.290 --> 34:31.120
'Cause I'm doing what
you asked me to --

34:31.120 --> 34:32.920
taking care of her

34:32.920 --> 34:33.920
while you're out there
lying about

34:33.920 --> 34:35.750
being at your sister's.

34:35.750 --> 34:37.920
I know what you're doing.

34:37.920 --> 34:39.420
She's doing the same thing,

34:39.420 --> 34:40.670
but no other kid

34:40.670 --> 34:42.580
is gonna replace
the one you lost.

34:42.580 --> 34:44.830
So here's what
you're gonna do.

34:44.830 --> 34:46.580
Delete this e-mail.

34:46.580 --> 34:50.330
Even if Vivian responds,
forget her, the kid.

34:50.330 --> 34:53.920
Go upstairs to your wife
and love her.

34:53.920 --> 34:55.750
'Cause that's what
she needs right now --

34:55.750 --> 35:00.580
a husband to let her know
she's not alone anymore,

35:00.580 --> 35:02.670
'cause she has you.

35:02.670 --> 35:10.040
♪♪

35:10.040 --> 35:17.620
♪♪

35:17.620 --> 35:20.330
I'm home, Annie.

35:20.330 --> 35:25.620
♪♪

35:25.620 --> 35:30.620
♪♪

35:30.620 --> 35:32.710
[ Sniffles ]

35:32.710 --> 35:40.460
♪♪

35:40.460 --> 35:47.880
♪♪

35:54.500 --> 35:57.580
I have something
I need to tell you.

35:58.540 --> 36:02.380
Your dad said
I had to protect you

36:02.380 --> 36:04.170
from your worst instincts.

36:06.040 --> 36:08.540
He's wrong,

36:08.540 --> 36:10.830
'cause I'm the one sticking
my nose in all of this,

36:10.830 --> 36:12.710
even when
you begged me to stop.

36:12.710 --> 36:15.710
And now I'm the guy
who makes jokes

36:15.710 --> 36:18.670
about wanting Gabriel dead.

36:18.670 --> 36:22.040
So maybe you need to protect me
from my worst instincts.

36:22.040 --> 36:26.580
♪♪

36:26.580 --> 36:28.750
[ Sighs ]

36:28.750 --> 36:30.750
Maybe we can protect
each other.

36:30.750 --> 36:37.420
♪♪

36:37.420 --> 36:44.080
♪♪

36:44.080 --> 36:46.250
What --
what are you doing?

36:46.250 --> 36:48.710
I'm too freaked out
to be alone right now.

36:48.710 --> 36:50.380
Well, I mean,
you are alone.

36:50.380 --> 36:51.790
We're --
We're all alone.

36:53.380 --> 36:54.620
Sorry.

36:56.580 --> 36:59.750
You know what's funny
about us?

36:59.750 --> 37:01.040
We're both disasters

37:01.040 --> 37:02.710
when it comes to picking people
to hook up with.

37:02.710 --> 37:04.620
We picked each other.

37:04.620 --> 37:06.040
Need I say more?

37:07.710 --> 37:09.380
You can...

37:09.380 --> 37:12.250
You can sleep
on this side,

37:12.250 --> 37:15.960
feet to feet
and no funny business.

37:15.960 --> 37:17.460
[ Scoffs ]

37:17.460 --> 37:26.830
♪♪

37:26.830 --> 37:36.460
♪♪

37:36.460 --> 37:45.830
♪♪

37:45.830 --> 37:55.330
♪♪

37:57.790 --> 38:03.790
♪♪

38:03.790 --> 38:09.830
♪♪

38:09.830 --> 38:11.500
[ Mouse double-clicks ]

38:11.500 --> 38:12.830
♪♪

38:12.830 --> 38:15.290
Sam: Dear Vivian, I know
I'm the last person

38:15.290 --> 38:17.670
you want to hear from
right now.

38:17.670 --> 38:19.620
[ Mouse clicking ]

38:19.620 --> 38:21.120
I tried to stay away,
I really did,

38:21.120 --> 38:25.830
but 11 years
is long enough.

38:25.830 --> 38:28.830
[ Baby cries ]

38:28.830 --> 38:30.960
That's why I came
to see you,

38:30.960 --> 38:34.000
to make things right
with you and him.

38:34.000 --> 38:38.580
[ Baby crying ]

38:38.580 --> 38:39.920
Hey.

38:39.920 --> 38:44.830
[ Baby coos ]
[ Exhales sharply ]

38:44.830 --> 38:47.250
It just breaks my heart
to know

38:47.250 --> 38:50.250
he grew up without a father
because of my failures.

38:50.250 --> 38:57.380
♪♪

38:57.380 --> 39:04.580
♪♪

39:04.580 --> 39:11.750
♪♪

39:11.750 --> 39:13.670
I did this.

39:13.670 --> 39:16.710
Okay?

39:16.710 --> 39:18.380
It was all me.

39:18.380 --> 39:20.380
No.

39:22.290 --> 39:24.540
He was gonna die
either way.

39:24.540 --> 39:27.210
♪♪

39:27.210 --> 39:28.880
You just saved him
some pain.

39:28.880 --> 39:32.210
♪♪

39:32.210 --> 39:34.420
I can tell
he's a good kid, though.

39:34.420 --> 39:36.460
I knew that
the minute I saw him.

39:36.460 --> 39:43.250
♪♪

39:43.250 --> 39:49.750
♪♪

39:49.750 --> 39:55.960
♪♪

39:55.960 --> 39:57.710
Hey.

39:57.710 --> 39:59.830
Hi.

39:59.830 --> 40:01.750
Can I have my ball back?

40:01.750 --> 40:05.960
♪♪

40:05.960 --> 40:08.330
He's a beautiful kid, Viv.

40:08.330 --> 40:10.420
All the best parts of you.
[ Knocking on door ]

40:10.420 --> 40:11.620
Grandma?

40:11.620 --> 40:13.830
♪♪

40:13.830 --> 40:16.170
[ Door opens ]
Gwen: Gabriel?

40:16.170 --> 40:22.830
♪♪

40:22.830 --> 40:29.750
♪♪

40:29.750 --> 40:31.750
[ Phone rings ]

40:31.750 --> 40:33.960
Woman: At the tone,
please record your message.

40:33.960 --> 40:35.330
[ Beeps ]
Hey.

40:37.580 --> 40:39.080
I screwed up.

40:40.620 --> 40:42.960
They found out who I am.

40:42.960 --> 40:45.210
Can you call me back?

40:45.210 --> 40:47.500
Sam: Maybe there's a chance
he'd like me in his life.

40:47.500 --> 40:48.710
[ Cellphone closes ]

40:48.710 --> 40:50.330
I know I'd like him
in mine.

40:52.830 --> 40:54.210
[ Knocking on door ]

40:54.210 --> 40:55.500
I'd be lying if I said

40:55.500 --> 40:57.620
I didn't think about us
sometimes,

40:57.620 --> 40:58.670
what could have been.

40:58.670 --> 41:00.620
[ Knocking on door ]

41:00.620 --> 41:02.710
I guess the truth is...

41:02.710 --> 41:04.330
I miss you, Viv.

41:04.330 --> 41:06.120
[ Knocking on door ]

41:07.460 --> 41:10.290
I miss how we were together.

41:10.290 --> 41:12.170
[ Knocking on door ]

41:14.120 --> 41:15.960
I miss who I was with you.

41:15.960 --> 41:20.670
♪♪

41:20.670 --> 41:22.080
Do I know you?

41:22.080 --> 41:23.170
♪♪

41:23.170 --> 41:24.670
I'm a friend
of Annalise's.

41:26.540 --> 41:27.830
Looks like the good times
didn't last too long.

41:27.830 --> 41:29.330
Her kid's here.

41:29.330 --> 41:31.540
You're going to
help me with this.

41:32.500 --> 41:34.710
That's why I'm writing this.

41:34.710 --> 41:37.330
Because I couldn't live
with myself

41:37.330 --> 41:39.670
if I didn't at least try
to be in our son's life

41:39.670 --> 41:43.000
and your life.

41:43.000 --> 41:46.500
So this is me trying.

41:46.500 --> 41:48.000
You owe me nothing.

41:48.000 --> 41:50.670
I owe you everything.

41:50.670 --> 41:52.250
But please know this.

41:52.250 --> 41:56.080
I've never stopped
loving you.

41:56.080 --> 41:59.670
All my love, Sam.

41:59.670 --> 42:02.170
♪♪

42:02.170 --> 42:05.620
He never deserved you,
Annalise.

42:05.620 --> 42:11.210
♪♪

42:11.210 --> 42:16.710
♪♪

42:28.380 --> 42:30.380
♪♪

42:35.620 --> 42:42.580
♪♪

42:42.580 --> 42:49.920
♪♪
